Why the change in time format?
Changed to milliseconds instead of seconds, I may have to do this change in previous commit
Should there be some sort of validation that the T* is the same type as the entry before dynamic casting? Or at least verify dumpEntry is not null?
Do we know this is a Resource dump?
Need to change, just moved the existing code

This confused me a bit, I assume this is what's meant?
"new entry is not a duplicate that has already completed"
We won't break here and continue to make sure another entry with same source id is not present. Updating the comment
Really trying to get away from InternalFailure and instead use better defined errors. Unless you really think this is a "never should happen" type code path.
This is in the existing code, this may not happen but if at all this happens it is better to get a small error log dump
Acknowledged
createAndNotify seems like a better name here? Just calling it notify makes me think it's only job is to notify listeners of a new dump.
Yes may be createOrUpdateHostEntry? Because the 'notify' is coming from the host, and now the factory needs to create a new entry or update an existing entry
Define these in a header somewhere for improved readability and in case they are used elsewhere?
Done
Ahh, yep, should be in a common header vs. defined throughout code.
Done
